{"word":"Ἰσραήλ","slug":"Ἰσραήλ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Ἰσραήλ, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Heb.\">Heb.</a>, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ etym.\">etym.</a> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ mng.\">mng.</a> uncertain] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ indecl.\">indecl.</a> <b>Israel<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> the patriarch Jacob <b><a href='B:470 10:6'>Mt 10:6</a>; <a href='B:490 1:16'>Lk 1:16</a>; <a href='B:510 2:36'>Ac 2:36</a>; <a href='B:520 9:27'>Ro 9:27b</a>; <a href='B:540 3:7'>2 Cor 3:7</a>; <a href='B:570 3:5'>Phil 3:5</a>; <a href='B:650 8:10'>Hb 8:10</a>; <a href='B:730 2:14'>Rv 2:14</a>; <a href='B:730 7:4'>7:4</a>; <a href='B:730 21:12'>21:12</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> the people of Israel <b><a href='B:470 2:6'>Mt 2:6</a>; <a href='B:480 12:29'>Mk 12:29</a></b> (of the gospels, Mk is unique with but one use of the term <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:Ἰσραήλ\">Ἰσραήλ</a></el>); <b><a href='B:490 1:54'>Lk 1:54</a>; <a href='B:500 1:31'>J 1:31</a>, <a href='B:500 1:49'>49</a>; <a href='B:510 1:6'>Ac 1:6</a>; <a href='B:510 4:10'>4:10</a>; <a href='B:520 9:6'>Ro 9:6a</a></b> (in a sententious statement), <b>27a; <a href='B:530 10:18'>1 Cor 10:18</a>; <a href='B:560 2:12'>Eph 2:12</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>3.</pp></b> believers within God’s promise system as authentic Israelites<b> <a href='B:520 9:6'>Ro 9:6b</a>; <a href='B:550 6:16'>Gal 6:16</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἰσόψυχος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:Ἰσραηλίτης\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}